{% comment %}
dev-story-mining — standalone base view. Mirrors stories/bugfix/views/base.pongo
and the block contract in docs/stories/story-style.md §2.

Consulted only when this story runs STANDALONE. When imported under a hub
story, the AppRenderer resolves `extends: "base"` against the HOST's base.

Block contract:
  status   — top status line: job · cycle · judge mode
  heading  — room title (default: state.description)
  body     — main content (prose, kv, code)
  choices  — action list
  footer   — optional bottom matter

The phase rooms use a flattened typed-element view (banner + choice) rather
than `extends: base` because a `choice:` element cannot live inside a
`blocks:` map — same idiom as stories/bugfix/rooms/reproducing.yaml.
{% endcomment %}
{% block status %}{{ world.job|default:"(no job)" }}  ·  cycle {{ world.cycle }}  ·  judge {{ world.judge_mode }}{% endblock %}

{% block heading %}{{ state.description }}{% endblock %}

{% block body %}{% endblock %}

{% block choices %}{% endblock %}
{% block footer %}{% endblock %}
